com.tozny.e3db

Interface Result<R>

  • Type Parameters:
    R - The type of the value returned when an operation completes successfully.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ErrorResult, ValueResult

    public interface Result<R>
    Carries the result of an asynchronous E3DB operation.

    This interface represents whether an asynchronous operation completed successfully or resulted in an error.

    If an error occured, the isError() method will return true. In that case, use asError() to inspect the error that occurred.

    Otherwise, the asValue() method will return a value representing the result of the operation (which varies depending on the operation performed).

    See the documentation for Client for more information about asynchronous operations.
